slide.title: Practising Identifying Impact, Outcomes, and Outputs statements

vectordata.alttext: Statement 5: Improved climate-adapted sustainable livelihoods for low-income women, men, and non-binary people affiliated with participating agroforestry cooperatives in the municipality of Santa Adilia
Statement 2: Increased adoption of climate-adapted production practices by agroforestry cooperatives
Statement 3: Enhanced gender-sensitive and inclusive business management capacity on the part of the agroforestry cooperatives
Statement 4: Gender-sensitive agricultural extension support provided on climate-adapted agroforestry practices
Statement 1: Gender-sensitive technical assistance provided to cooperative leaders on financial, marketing, and governance topics
Statement 6: Gender awareness workshops delivered to cooperative members and leaders
In order, the correct answers are: output, outcome, outcome, output, impact and output

The impact is a long-term desired result, a vision of a “big picture”. An outcome describes the short or medium-term effects of an intervention’s output(s). An output is the result of a completed activity.
